This is the OpenPandora vendor maintained package configuration layer for use with Openembedded/Ångström. 
This provides the branding, stylistic and functional overlay to stock Ångström to match that in shipped 
'official' firmware images.

It should be used with openembedded-core (not old-style org.openembedded.dev).

More information can be found at:

                    http://www.openpandora.org/
                    
Build scripts to support making a firmware image for the OpenPandora can be found at:

                    https://github.com/openpandora/openpandora-oe-environment

This layer depends on:

URI: git://git.openembedded.org/openembedded-core
branch: master
revision: HEAD

URI: git://git.openembedded.org/meta-openembedded
branch: master
revision: HEAD

URI: git://git.angstrom-distribution.org/meta-angstrom
branch: master
revision: HEAD

URI: git://git.angstrom-distribution.org/meta-texasinstruments
branch: master
revision: HEAD

URI: git://github.com/openpandora/meta-openpandora.git
branch: master
revision: HEAD

It is preferred that people raise pull requests using GIThub by forking the appropriate tree:

                   https://github.com/openpandora/
                   (More info on achieving this can be found at http://help.github.com/send-pull-requests/)

Alternatively you can send patches to OpenPandora Firmware mailing list:
                   
                   firmware-dev@openpandora.org
                   http://openpandora.org/cgi-bin/mailman/listinfo/firmware-dev

If sending patches to the mailing list please try and ensure they are produced using 'git format-patch'
                   
Layer maintainers: John Willis <John.Willis at distant-earth.com>
                   Michael Mrozek <EvilDragon at openpandora.org>
